  "body": " Simplify .   In this expression, there is no operation of addition or subtraction inside parentheses, so the Distributive Law does not apply. In fact, we can drop all parentheses, it is helpful (for me, anyway) to write in all multiplication symbols: We can juggle the order of the four factors because we have the Commutative Property of Multiplication: Applying arithmetic in the first two factors gives us , and we can apply for the third and fourth factors: and finally, the exponont is a reducible fraction: In summary,    "
